from alan the hepburn subject re hockey and the hispanic community in article stacey a ros write in rickc richard casare write you have a hard time sell any sport to a community that ca play it on account of availability or financial reason hockey be pretty much a sport for the white and well off what white ye well off definitely not hockey season ticket owner have the lowest average income of any of the fmy major north american sport do you have a basi for thi claim try these stat take from playboy magazine june percentage of pro football fan who have attend college percentage of pro baseball fan who have attend college percentage of pro basketball fan who have attend college percentage of pro hockey fan who have attend college percentage of pro football fan who earn more than percentage of pro baseball fan who make more than percentage of pro basketball fan who make more than percentage of pro hackey fan who make more than and think of where the majority of hockey player come from from a farm out in boondock saskatchewan or weedville albertum the biggest advantage that kid from boondock or weedville have be the availability of ice in the san jose area we have a population of and that population be serve by ice arena in contrast kamloop british columbium ha a population of about and ha rink there be also myriad pond pool etc that freeze in the winter down here it hard to find a kid without a bicycle up there it hard to find a kid without a pair of skate and before you say what do he know he from californium let me say that i wa bear and raise in trail british columbium a town of about with lot of ice in the winter my father do radio play by play for the local team the trail smokeater who by the way be the last canadian team to win the world championship back in i wa on skate almost a soon a i could walk and have be play recreational hockey for about year when wa the last time you saw a hockey league in the inner city the insurance alone be a big enough barrier the inner city be the only place that be poor i think the biggest barrier to hockey in the inner city be no ice to play on lack of ice be a big factor but cost be a bigger factor both my kid play for the santum clara valley hockey association and thi season which just end cost me per kid for membership in hockey usa plu per kid for club due the hockey usa fee cover exces medical insurance and the club due cover ice time official trophy etc other area have similar fee unles the city government subsidise some of the cost a stockton do by the way most ice arena be locate in what could be call the inner city area eastridge and vallco be exception redwood city rink be in an industrial area on bay rd near berkeley be near ashby and martin luther king stockton be in oak park sacramento be in an older section of downtown i forget the name of the street fresno be out on the edge of town just west of santum rosa be a nice rink but it in an older section of town dublin be outside of town off most of the rink be old and expensive to run with huge electric bill and insurance premium if you want to buy ice time expect to pay around per hmy at any of these rink some of them give you a minute hmy for ymy money other give you a minute hmy and include the resurface time in the fee alan hepburn a man do know what he know national semiconductor until he know what he do know santum clara ca alan thoma carlyle 